r heads, an education in their brains, and that they can pay their medical =
bills without fear of bankruptcy.
But a person=E2=80=99s labor can=E2=80=99t grow exponentially, it can=E2=80=
=99t possibly keep up with exponential growth, so we need to make sure that=
 it=E2=80=99s as easy as possible for Americans to become owners.=C2=A0
We did it once, with home ownership, and we need to do it again with divers=
ified portfolios of assets that mean that all Americans do well when any of=
 our fellow Americans do really well. Markets are global, consumer bases ar=
e global, potential outcomes are bigger than ever before: we should orient =
ourselves to ensure that as much ownership as possible ends up in the hands=
 of as many Americans as possible.=C2=A0
And yes, their pensions or retirement plans might own assets. That=E2=80=99=
