we need to stop focusing so much time worrying about protecting peoples&#82=
17; downsides and start spending more time working on getting more people m=
ore upside.</strong>&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; =
line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Put another way, there is more relat=
ive downside to not participating in upside than there is to the actual dow=
nside. As any equity investor will tell you, you can only lose 1x your mone=
y, but your upside is uncapped.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-s=
ize: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">We&#8217;re thinking like=
 a bunch of fixed income investors, worrying about what can go wrong, inste=
ad of thinking like venture capitalists, dreaming of what can go right! Tha=
t needs to change.</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-hei=
ght: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">From Main Street to the bleeding edge of the=
 internet, we need to make sure that Americans of all incomes are able to n=
ot just work for capital, but to put capital to work for them. We need to p=
rotect their digital property rights like their physical ones, and make it =
easy for them to earn upside in the projects in which they participate.&nbs=
p;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margi=
n: 0 0 1em 0;">Obviously, we need to make sure that people are well-compens=
ated for their labor, that they&#8217;re able to put food on the table, a r=
oof over their heads, an education in their brains, <em>and</em> that they =
can pay their medical bills without fear of bankruptcy.</p><p style=3D"colo=
r: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">But a p=
erson&#8217;s labor can&#8217;t grow exponentially, it can&#8217;t possibly=
 keep up with exponential growth, so we need to make sure that it&#8217;s a=
s easy as possible for Americans to become owners.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"col=
or: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">We did=
 it once, with home ownership, and we need to do it again with diversified =
portfolios of assets that mean that all Americans do well when any of our f=
ellow Americans do really well. Markets are global, consumer bases are glob=
al, potential outcomes are bigger than ever before: we should orient oursel=
ves to ensure that as much ownership as possible ends up in the hands of as=
 many Americans as possible.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size=
: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">And yes, their pensions or r=
etirement plans might own assets. That&#8217;s great. But this is as much a=
bout the <em>feeling</em> of upside as the upside itself. If America can ge=
t its swagger back, there&#8217;s no problem we can&#8217;t solve.&nbsp;</p=
><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 =
0 1em 0;">The old America would have treated COVID like a war to win togeth=
er instead of squabbling over basic facts. The old America would welcome th=
e opportunity to lead the world on climate, recognizing the huge financial =
and societal upside in doing so. The old America would make damn sure that =
web3 startups weren&#8217;t domiciling abroad to avoid restrictive regulati=
on. Our country&#8217;s strongest competitor is a bastion of centralized co=
ntrol; we should be using that to our advantage, counter-positioning, and m=
aking America the home of democratized ownership.</p><p style=3D"color: #1a=
1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">We need to pu=
sh upside and ownership to the edges. People who create value should be rew=
arded in assets whose value appreciates in-line with the value created. We =
need to fight capitalism with capitalism, and financialization with hyperfi=
nancialization.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-=
height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">We can revive the American Dream by <stro=
ng>making ownership an explicit economic strategy</strong>.</p><p style=3D"=
color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">The=
 <a href=3D"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkE2OhCAQhU_T7DQIiPaCxWzmGg=
ahUNIKBoo23n7odjFJpX7z8iqf0QhLTJc6YkbySRNeB6gAZ94AERIpGdLkreokG3kvnsQqYbuxH=
4nPk0sAu_abwlSAHGXevNHoY_gqKGU9WZW0shu4E0_BLeNP089gnrJj1vUwS-hvX12sh2BAwRvS=
